6.Ne5  Bb7  7.O-O  Nf6  → @@StartFEN@@rnbqkbnr/p4ppp/2p1p3/1p6/2pP4/5NP1/PP2PPBP/RNBQK2R w KQkq - 0 6@@EndFEN@@  6.O-O  Nf6  7.Ne5  Bb7  .   To summarize: if White starts with  6.O-O  , we play the generally useful move  6...Nf6  , while after @@StartFEN@@rnbqkbnr/p4ppp/2p1p3/1p6/2pP4/5NP1/PP2PPBP/RNBQK2R w KQkq - 0 6@@EndFEN@@  6.Ne5  or  6.a4  we need to react on the queenside first, as it's a direct attack that needs to be addressed. White will eventually castle and the various move orders lead to the same positions. }
