cxd5 { 11...e5  12.Nxc6!  is the main trap.  That's why we take on d5 first. }
12. exd5 e5 13. Ndxb5 exf4 14. d6
{ This is how White wins back the piece − it won't yield an advantage though. }
14... Bxd6 15. Bxa8 Bc5
{ White is simply losing as ...Bc8-a6 is a huge threat. White can defuse that threat with  16.Bg2  , though  16...Ba6  is still not bad at all, but here  16...Ne5!  is huge as the knight is headed for the giant  outpost on d3. The engine believes this position to be -7. While that may be an outlandish evaluation in human terms, there is no denying Black has a crushing initiative here. }
