d5 { The only logical follow-up, but it just falls short. } 10... Nf6 11. dxe6
fxe6
{ The most ambitious reply, fighting for an advantage.  11...Qxd1  allows White to even the material balance with the intermediate  12.exf7+  Kxf7  13.Rxd1  when  13...Re8  14.e5  Bxc3  15.bxc3  Ne4  is equal according to the engines, but obviously simply a very double-edged endgame. }
