{ Preparing to unpin with ...Nc5-a6 while @@StartFEN@@6k1/2r1qppp/4p3/2n5/4P3/2Q2N2/5PPP/2R3K1 w - - 2 24@@EndFEN@@  24.Qa5  Ra7!  reminds White there is some danger on the back rank as well.  Concluding our investigation into 6.e4, I'd like to point out how this line is very much underexplored compared to the bigger brother 6.e3. Nevertheless, the resulting positions are very rich and not easy to play. Therefore we would recommend studying these lines carefully. Most importantly, theoretically speaking, Black is in excellent shape. }
