{ It is important to get the move orders right. For all the subtle nuances, please see the Informational dedicated to this topic. }
8. Ne5
{ Not a move we should take lightly, though it has hardly ever been seen at the highest level. White wants to follow up with Qd1-f3 in order to press the weak points on c6 and f7. }
