{ Knights before bishops.   Instead,  8...Bb7  9.axb5  Bxc3  10.bxc3  cxb5  11.Rb1  Qd5  12.Qg4  may still be alright for Black after  12...Nd7!  with the crazy point  13.Qxg7  Nxe5  14.Qxh8  Nd3+!  15.Bxd3  Qxg2  16.Bf1  Qg6  and both of White's rooks are hanging, but the text move is much simpler. }
9. axb5 { Not the logical follow-up to White's previous move. } 9... Bxc3 10.
Bxc3 cxb5 11. Qf3 Ra6 { This is very bad news. } 12. b3 b4 13. Bb2 c3
{ White's position is horrible. } *

