21. Bc2 Qg4 22. h3 Qh5
{ The queen is fine on the kingside, where it can sometimes participate in an attack against the king on g1. }
23. e4 a4
{ Time to cut the line short. In Nekhaev-Lebedev, ICCF 2017 the players drew on move 39, but it's obvious that there is a very sharp position on the board. As usual, we find our game easier − we have plans including ...Ne7-g6, ...Rd8-b8 and, as always, pushing the pawns. }
