20... Bxf3
{ Safest as both  20...Ne8  21.Nxd4  Nxe5  22.Nf5  and @@StartFEN@@r1r3k1/1b1n1ppp/5n2/p1q1P3/1p1p4/3B1N2/1B1Q1PPP/R3R1K1 b - - 1 20@@EndFEN@@  20...Nd5  21.Bxd4  are messier. }
21. Bxd4 { Using the fact there is a discovered check in the position. } 21...
Qxd4 { Falling for the trap.  21...Qd5  22.gxf3  g6!  isn't bad either. } 22.
Bxh7+ Nxh7 23. Qxd4 Bc6
{ With three pieces for the queen and two connected passed pawns, Black is in good shape. }
