{ Pinning the knight in order to get the move ...b7-b5 back on the cards. Here we see a major difference with the Slav @@StartFEN@@rnbqkbnr/pppppppp/8/8/8/8/PPPPPPPP/RNBQKBNR w KQkq - 0 1@@EndFEN@@  1.d4  d5  2.c4  c6  3.Nf3  Nf6  4.Nc3  dxc4  5.a4  where Black also takes on c4 but is unable to hold on to that pawn for very long.  Having played ...e7-e6 instead of ...Ng8-f6 allows us to pin the knight on c3 with 5...Bb4 and follow it up with ...b7-b5, thus making it much harder for White to regain the pawn. }
