7... Qxd1+ 8. Kxd1 Bf5
{ Even with the queens exchanged, White's king still feels uncomfortable on d1. }
9. f4 Nd7 10. Bd2 O-O-O
{ White doesn't get much reason for optimism. Black threatens ...f7-f6 and has fantastic pieces. }
