{ A way to put pressure along the d-file without yet determining the position of the king. That is also the downside of the move, as the king on e1 will prove to hamper White's play. Nevertheless, it's a very serious try. }
12... O-O-O 13. Qa3 Kb7 14. Nf3
{ This is how a recent computer game continued. } 14... e5
{ White decided to repeat. } 15. Rd2 Qb1+ 16. Rd1 Qe4 17. Rd2 Qb1+ 18. Rd1 Qe4
{ 1/2-1/2 RubiChess 2.0-Igel 3.0.0, CCRL 2021. Continuing the game can also backfire. }
