10... e5 { As usual, it is not advisable to take the pawn. } 11. Bxe5 Nb4 12.
Qd2 a5
{ Surprisingly, it is only after this move that Black can really claim to have a big advantage. It is important to avoid  12...Qxh1  13.O-O-O  Bf5  14.Qxb4  and White is better. Keep this line in mind when we continue down the main line! }
13. a3 Qxh1 14. O-O-O Bf5
{ With the moves 12...a5 and 13.a3 included, this position suddenly looks much different! White can't take on b4 with the queen now. }
