{ A spectacular quiet move, simply preparing to castle queenside while a rook is hanging on h1. }
10... Qe4
{ More shocking is that this retreat could actually be working! Black spends two tempi to pick up the g2-pawn, which in the normal order of how chess works should not be allowed! Chess is a concrete game though, as we are about to see. }
11. O-O-O
{ The most obvious move, White wants to do dark things on the d-file. } 11...
e5 12. Bxe5 { Or  12.Qg5  Qf4+!  getting the queens off. } 12... Bf5
{ Preventing mate on d8 while threatening mate on b1! } 13. Bd3 Qxd3 14. Qxd3
Bxd3 15. Bxg7 { 15.Rxd3  f6  is clearly better for Black. } 15... Nb4 16. a3
Na2+ 17. Kd2 O-O-O
{ White would do best to fish for repetition with  18.Ke1  Re8+  19.Kd2  Rd8  . }
18. Ke3 Nh6 19. Bxh8 Ng4+ 20. Kf3 Be4+ { White's position is very dangerous. }
