15. exd4
{ 15.Qxd4  is not very critical and gives us a good game after the simple  15...bxa3  . }
15... Ne4
{ Releasing the f8-rook, reminding White we really don't miss the f-pawn! } 16.
Bxe4 { The start of a highly tactical variation. } 16... dxe4 17. Re1 Rxf3
{ The only way to proceed, and a good one. White's king position is breached. }
18. gxf3 Qg5+ 19. Kh1 exf3 20. Rg1
{ It looks like our attack has been repelled, but a second wave is incoming. }
20... Qh4 21. axb4 Nf6
{ No time to be thinking about rooks! It's about the king on h1. } 22. Rxa8
{ 22.Nd2!  is the only move to stay in the game. } 22... Ng4 23. Rxc8+ Kf7 24.
Rc7+ Ke8
{ Two rooks up, White will be running out of checks, after which mate is imminent. }
*

