{ We intend to play ...Nf6-h5-f4 next, launching an initiative on the kingside. }
18. Nbd2
{ After  18.axb4  , we don't even recapture but execute our plan with  18...Nh5  and ...Nf4. }
18... Nxd2
{ A small change of plan!  18...Nh5  is possible here as well but after  19.Nxe4  dxe4  20.Ne5  it doesn't look like we have enough play on the kingside. }
19. Qxd2 { Giving up on the a-pawn can't be leading to an advantage. } 19...
bxa3 20. Rfe1 Ne4 21. Qa2 Ra8 22. cxd5
{ White's best shot, trying to make use of the various pins in the position. }
22... cxd5 23. b4 Qf7 24. Re3
{ Threatening our a3-pawn. Taking it though leads nowhere as we are about to see. }
24... h6 25. Rxa3 Rxa3 26. Qxa3 Ng5
{ The knight cannot be taken due to ...Qxf2, meaning we win back the pawn by taking on f3 next move. }
