{ Let's take the pawn. White now has a choice.  A@@EndBracket@@  10.Qxb3  Qxd4  sacrifices a second pawn, which yields enough compensation, but 'two pawns are two pawns'.   B@@EndBracket@@  10.Bb2  looks like White's best bet. We are fine with precise play, though.   C@@EndBracket@@  10.axb5  axb5  11.Rxa8  Bxa8  is an alternative, after which White can decide between the two concepts of  12.Qxb3  or  12.Bb2  again. Let's check all these options. }
10. Bb2
{ White covers the d-pawn first and intends to capture the b-pawn later. GM Srinath Narayanan recommended this line in his Chessable course Lifetime Repertoires: The Catalan − a good choice as Black needs to be precise against it. }
