{ Taking the pawn in the most critical move. In the context of our repertoire, the move  3...c6  also makes a lot of sense. It will very likely continue with  4.Nf3  dxc4  or @@StartFEN@@rnbqkbnr/pp3ppp/2p1p3/3p4/2PP4/6P1/PP2PP1P/RNBQKBNR w KQkq - 0 4@@EndFEN@@  4.Bg2  dxc4  5.Nf3  , when we'd transpose to the line @@StartFEN@@rnbqkbnr/ppp2ppp/4p3/3p4/2PP4/8/PP2PPPP/RNBQKBNR w KQkq - 0 3@@EndFEN@@  3.Nf3  c6  4.g3  dxc4  5.Bg2  , which is part of our repertoire. Our suggestion @@StartFEN@@rnbqkbnr/ppp2ppp/4p3/3p4/2PP4/8/PP2PPPP/RNBQKBNR w KQkq - 0 3@@EndFEN@@  3.g3  dxc4  will also transpose to these lines most of the time but allows some interesting possible deviations. }
4. Bg2
{ White also has  4.Nf3  , when it is easiest for us to play  4...c6  and transpose to the line @@StartFEN@@rnbqkbnr/ppp2ppp/4p3/3p4/2PP4/8/PP2PPPP/RNBQKBNR w KQkq - 0 3@@EndFEN@@  3.Nf3  c6  4.g3  dxc4  . Alternatively, you could play @@StartFEN@@rnbqkbnr/ppp2ppp/4p3/8/2pP4/5NP1/PP2PP1P/RNBQKB1R b KQkq - 1 4@@EndFEN@@  4...c5!?  , which after  5.Bg2  leads to a line that we mention as a possible alternative against 4.Bg2. After @@StartFEN@@rnbqkbnr/ppp2ppp/4p3/8/2pP4/6P1/PP2PP1P/RNBQKBNR w KQkq - 0 4@@EndFEN@@  4.Bg2  c5!?  @@StartBracket@@we recommend  4...c6  , which is more typical@@EndBracket@@ @@StartFEN@@rnbqkbnr/pp3ppp/4p3/2p5/2pP4/6P1/PP2PPBP/RNBQK1NR w KQkq - 0 5@@EndFEN@@  5.Nf3  , the same position is reached. }
4... c6
{ We prepare ...b5 and invite an almost mandatory transposition to the line @@StartFEN@@rnbqkbnr/ppp2ppp/4p3/3p4/2PP4/8/PP2PPPP/RNBQKBNR w KQkq - 0 3@@EndFEN@@  3.Nf3  c6  4.g3  dxc4  5.Bg2  , as White now has no reasonable alternative to 5.Nf3.   We want to mention that Black has a good option here with  4...c5  . After this move,  5.Nf3  Nc6  is a logical continuation. White has tried a few lines against this setup, but Black confidently equalizes. A practical drawback for Black is replies like  6.Qa4  cxd4  7.Nxd4  Qxd4  8.Bxc6+  , when the game gets simplified substantially, it is tough to get a fighting position. We felt that the transposition into 'triangle' style lines is the best way to stir up a fight and saves us some theoretical workload. }
5. Nf3 b5
{ And we have transposed to the line @@StartFEN@@rnbqkbnr/ppp2ppp/4p3/3p4/2PP4/8/PP2PPPP/RNBQKBNR w KQkq - 0 3@@EndFEN@@  3.Nf3  c6  4.g3  dxc4  5.Bg2  b5  , which is examined in a different chapter. }
