{ White can't take on h7, as  10.Rxh7  Rxh7  11.Bxh7  g6  traps the greedy bishop. }
10... Nf6 11. O-O-O h6
{ We finally need to protect h7. After this necessary move, we need to make a key decision soon. It's possible to play kingside castling, but it looks a bit scary due to the open h-file.  A good alternative is to play ...Qe7, ...Bd7, and ...O-O-O, when our king looks safer. In the long run, Black chances are preferable due to the bishop pair. Therefore, we'd advise playing for queenside castling. }
