{ The move  7...Qb6  is fine, too. You have to avoid  7...Qc7??  , though. This is surprisingly awful after  8.Ng5  , when you have no good way  to cover e6,  as  8...Qc8  9.Nxe6!  wins immediately for White.  After @@StartFEN@@rn1qkbnr/pp4pp/2p1p3/3p1p2/3P4/1Q2PN2/PPP2PPP/RNB2RK1 b kq - 1 7@@EndFEN@@  7...Qc8  we reach an interesting and unexplored position. We continue  with ...Nf6 and ...Bd6, reaching a typical Stonewall formation, but without the potential worry of a bad light-squared bishop. }
