{ The typical reply to Qb3 in this chapter. We don't need to cover b7 and defend actively. Now White's most popular move is  6.Nc3  , when  6...Nf6  transposes to the line @@StartFEN@@rn1qkbnr/ppp2ppp/4p3/3p1b2/2PP4/5N2/PP2PPPP/RNBQKB1R w KQkq - 0 4@@EndFEN@@  4.Nc3  Nf6  5.cxd5  exd5  6.Qb3  Nc6  . We need to check some other options, though.  White also frequently covers b4 with  @@StartFEN@@r2qkbnr/ppp2ppp/2n5/3p1b2/3P4/1Q3N2/PP2PPPP/RNB1KB1R w KQkq - 2 6@@EndFEN@@  6.Bd2  or  6.a3  , while  6.Qxb7?  fails, but requires a precise response. }
