{ Stockfish suggests this miracle defense. A more human approach like  8.Na3  Rb8  9.Qxa7  Nc6  10.Qa4  Bb4+  11.Bd2  dxe4  wins quite easily for Black. }
8... Nf6
{ We can't play  8...Nc2+??  9.Kd1  Nxa1  due to  10.Nxd7  , when we have no good reply. }
9. Bg5 Qb8
{ Not exactly the obvious move, but let's have a brief look at the alternative  9...Rb8  , which suggests itself. After  10.Qxa7  Nc2+  11.Kd1  Nxa1  12.Nxd7  Kxd7  Black is a rook up, but White has an attack that is impossible to assess with absolute certainty. It looks like a draw@@StartBracket@@!@@EndBracket@@  with the best play, therefore we suggest 9...Qb8, which leads to a position with a slight edge that is simple to play. }
10. Qxb8+ Rxb8
{ Alright, we have reached a somewhat sane position. White can't defend against both ...Nxe4 and ...Nc2+. }
11. Kd1 Nxe4 12. Be3 c5
{ Black has the better chances here, seeing that White's position is not well coordinated. }
