{ The best defense. As mentioned already,  13.O-O?  Re6  14.Qb5  Rg6  already starts a devastating attack on White's king. The point of @@StartFEN@@r2qr1k1/p1p2ppp/2Q5/3p1b2/3Pn3/2P1P3/P3BPPP/R1B1K2R w KQ - 2 13@@EndFEN@@  13.c4  is to answer  13...Re6??  with  14.Qxd5  . }
13... Bd7
{ A powerful and important move! The great point is that White now can't grab the d5-pawn. }
14. Qxd5 { This pawn is poisoned. Let's check how we are going to prove that. }
14... c6 { We attack the queen... and it has only one safe square to go to. }
15. Qh5 g6 16. Qf3
{ The move  16.Qh6  loses similarly after  16...Qa5+  17.Kf1  Qc3  , invading with decisive effect. }
16... Qa5+ 17. Kf1 Qc3 { Invasion time! } 18. Rb1 Qc2 19. Ra1 Rab8
{ And that's it. White has no defense at all against the simple threat ...Qc3, trapping the rook in the corner. }
