{ White should damage our pawn structure before we can play ...Nbd7. White sometimes takes on b6 first; we'll check this option on the next move. }
8... gxf6
{ It's possible to take on b3, of course. We suggest not taking just yet, as White might still capture on b6, which is very much welcome. Better seems to be  9.e3  , though. We'll check both moves now. }
9. e3 Nd7 { 'Please take on b6!' } 10. Be2
{ White sticks to the plan of not taking on b6. } 10... Qxb3
