11. axb3 a6
{ A good move that makes the a8-rook mobile. This endgame offers equal chances. Our kingside pawn structure is damaged, but it is unclear how White might benefit from it.  White could try to gain control of f5 − think of Nh4 and Bd3, followed by Nf5. This looks nice, but the knight on f5 is not attacking anything at all. We can try to open the queenside and play against the doubled pawn in the long run. We also have the bishop pair as a long-term asset. }
