8. Qb5+
{ This looks like the most human move, probably. White retreats the queen with a check and picks up the c4-pawn. }
8... c6 9. Qxc4
{ The queen raid has netted White a pawn, but we have excellent compensation. The offside knight on a3 is a substantial problem for our opponent. }
9... Be4
{ The exclaim is used to emphasize the importance of the idea. We'd cover c6, but more importantly, prepare ...Bd5. However, it needs to be said that you don't need to play the move immediately, as White's coordination issues are tough to solve. Starting with  9...Be7  , for example, also works well. }
