11. Rc1 { White wants to pick up c4 with the rook. } 11... Ra6
{ We need to play this move or  11...Nd5  , avoiding  11...Qxc6?  12.Qxc6+  bxc6  13.Bxc7  , when White is much better. }
12. Rxc4 Rxc6 13. Rxc6 bxc6
{ Compared to @@StartFEN@@r3k2r/1ppq1ppp/2N1pn2/p7/QbpP1B2/4P3/PP2KPPP/2R2B1R b kq - 2 11@@EndFEN@@  11...Qxc6?  , we were able to avoid the trade of queens. This is essential, as White still needs to coordinate the position due to the misplaced king. In such a scenario, we'd like to have a queen on the board. }
14. a3 Bd6 15. Qxa5 O-O
{ Stockfish evaluates this position as equal, but we are happy with Black's chances. White's position is not easy to play as the king is a constant worry in the long run. }
